<H3> <TI>   IAEA Inspectors Arrive in Pyongyang </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IAEA Inspectors Arrive in Pyongyang </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1705131994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1301 GMT 17 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1705131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 17 (XINHUA) -- Three inspectors of 
the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) arrived here today 
to begin a further inspection of nuclear facilities of the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK). 
  Eyewitness saw more than ten boxes belonging to the 
inspectors at the airport. The inspectors told XINHUA that the 
boxes contained equipment for the inspection. 
  However, they refused to reveal any details about the 
inspection but said that their activities would last about one 
week. 
  In March, the IAEA inspected the Yongbyon Radioactive 
Chemical Laboratory which is located 100 km north of Pyongyong. 
But the agency is not satisfied with the results and so 
inspectors have to carry out another inspection, according to 
reports. 
  However, the reports say that the new inspection will not 
include monitoring the change of fuel rods at the 5-megawatt 
nuclear reactor. 

</TEXT>

