<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yunnan Governor He Zhiqiang Meets Burmese Leadership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yunnan Governor He Zhiqiang Meets Burmese Leadership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1705144994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1326 GMT 17 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1705144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yangon [Rangoon], May 17 (XINHUA) -- Myanmar 
[Burma] leader Senior General Than Shwe has stated that the 
economic relations between his country and China's Yunnan 
Province would be promoted further through strengthening the 
trade and economic cooperation between the two sides. 
  Senior General Than Shwe, chairman of State Law and Order 
Restoration Council (SLORC), made the remarks here today when he 
received Governor of Yunnan Province of China He Zhiqiang. 
  Present on the occasion were SLORC Vice-Chairman General 
Maung Aye [name and title as received], SLORC Secretary-1 
Lieutenant General Khin Nyunt, SLORC Secretary-2 Lieutenant 
General Tin Oo, Minister for National Planning and Economic 
Development Brig. General Abel, Foreign Minister Ohn Gyaw and 
Chinese Ambassador to Myanmar Liang Feng. 
  He Zhiqiang told the Myanmar leader that the relations on 
trade and economic cooperation between Yunnan and Myanmar are 
developing and friendship between China and Myanmar are also 
deepened further. 
  At the invitation of Minister for National Planning and 
Economic Development Brig. General Abel, an eight-member Yunnan 
delegation led by He Zhiqiang and accompanied by a 18-member 
economic cooperation mission of Yunnan Province arrived here on 
Monday to begin a 10-day visit to Myanmar. 

</TEXT>

