<H3> <TI>   Sihanouk Arrives for Medical Treatment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sihanouk Arrives for Medical Treatment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1805084894 Hong Kong AFP in English 0820 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> HK1805084894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 18 (AFP) -- Cambodia's King Norodom 
Sihanouk returned to Beijing Wednesday to resume medical 
treatment for a cancer that has spread to his bone marrow. 
  Although smiling and waving, King Sihanouk was clearly weak 
and had to be helped down the steps from the airplane after his 
flight landed at Beijing's international airport. 
  Citing "serious health problems" Sihanouk said last week 
that 
he needed to return to Beijing from Cambodia two weeks ahead of 
schedule. 
  The king spoke for several minutes with Chinese officials 
among the welcoming committee before being whisked away by 
limousine. 
  Sihanouk, 71, began chemotherapy and radiation treatment at 
a 
Beijing hospital in October folowing the discovery of a tumour 
near his prostate gland. 
  He has maintained homes in Beijing and the North Korean 
capital Pyongyang for several years. 

</TEXT>

