<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yangon [Rangoon], May 16 (XINHUA) -- Governor of 
Yunnan Province of China He Zhiqiang arrived here this afternoon 
for a ten-day visit to Myanmar [Burma]. 
  At the invitation of Minister for National Planning and 
Economic Development Brigadier-General Abel, the governor began 
the visit, accompanied by a 16-member trade and economy group. 
  He Zhiqiang's visit is aimed at strengthening traditional 
friendship, trade and economic cooperation with Myanmar, it is 
learnt. 
  Myanmar officially opened border trade with China's Yunnan 
province in 1988, and it is the first border trade station with 
neighboring countries for Myanmar. 

</TEXT>

