<H3> <TI>   Cambodia's Norodom Sihanouk Leaves for China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cambodia's Norodom Sihanouk Leaves for China </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1805055794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0527 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1805055794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh, May 18 (XINHUA) -- King Norodom Sihanouk 
of Cambodia left here this morning for Beijing, China, to resume 
treatment for cancer. 
  The king was accompanied by his wife Queen Monique. 
  They were seen off at the airport by first Prime Minister 
Norodom Ranariddh, Second Prime Minister Hun Sen, parliament 
speaker Chea Sim and Chinese Ambassador to Cambodia Xie Yue'e 
[name as received]. 
  The 72-year-old king made a surprise announcement last week 
that he would leave for China on May 18 to resume chemotherapy 
treatment for cancer. Originally, he had planned to stay in his 
country until June 2 and then pay his first official visit to 
China after becoming king. 
  King Sihanouk returned to Cambodia on April 8 after six 
months of treatment for cancer in Beijing. While in Cambodia, 
he launched a number of proposals for peace in order to hasten 
the national reconciliation process. 

</TEXT>

