<F P=102>   OW1705102794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0851 GMT 17 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1705102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Qingdao, May 17 (XINHUA) -- Construction of an Asian 
industrial park, a Sino-Singapore joint venture, is well under 
way in Qingdao City, Shandong Province, a favorite spot for 
Singapore investors. 
  Located in the Qingdao Economic and Technological 
Development 
Zone, the park covers an area of five square kilometers. 
  Plans are to develop one square kilometer in the first year 
and the rest in three years. 
  Upon completion, the park will mainly house high-tech 
industrial projects, a local official said. 
  As of May 14, Qingdao and Singapore had set up 83 joint 
ventures and cooperative projects with a total investment of 330 
million U.S. dollars. 
  Qingdao is one of China's 14 open coastal cities as well as 
a 
popular tourist attraction. 

</TEXT>

