<H3> <TI>   Singapore Becomes Second Largest Investor in Shandong </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Singapore Becomes Second Largest Investor in Shandong </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1705013894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0125 GMT 17 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1705013894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Weihai, May 17 (XINHUA) -- East China's Shandong 
Province has recently signed a contract with Singapore on a 200 
million U.S. dollar project for an "international city." 
  Located in Yantai city and covering an area of 658,000 
square 
meters, it is the biggest project wholly financed by Singapore. 
  According to the plan, the "city" will have facilities such 
as meeting center, exhibition center, education center, 
entertainment center, office buildings and luxury apartments. 
  Figures given at a press conference showed that Singapore 
injected over 100 million U.S. dollars into the province from 
January to March this year, jumping to second largest investor 
after Hong Kong. 
  Last year, the province absorbed a promised investment of 
390 
million U.S. dollars from Singapore, quadruple that of 1992. 

</TEXT>

