<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Visits Northern European Countries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihuan Visits Northern European Countries </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets Swedish Parliamentary Speaker </H4>

<F P=102> OW1405181094 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0210 
GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1405181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporters Xu Furui (6079 4395 3843) and Wu Ping (0702 </F>
1627)] 
  [Text] Stockholm, 10 May (XINHUA) -- Troedsson, speaker of 
the parliament of the Kingdom of Sweden, met with Li Ruihuan, 
visiting chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese 
People's Political Consultative Conference [CPPCC], in the 
parliament building this afternoon. In a friendly atmosphere, 
the two recalled the traditional friendship between China and 
Sweden and expressed their hope that the two countries will 
enjoy constantly growing bilateral relations. 
  Li Ruihuan said: Sino-Swedish exchanges date back to ancient 
times, and the Chinese and Swedish people have always had 
friendly feelings for each other. Sweden was one of the first 
of the group of Western countries which established diplomatic 
relations with New China, and the Chinese people have always 
spoken highly of this fact. Since the establishment of 
diplomatic relations, the two countries have attained remarkable 
achievements in exchanges and cooperation in all fields. I hope 
that bilateral relations will grow further on the basis of 
equality and mutual benefit. 
  Li Ruihuan said: China has achieved fairly great economic 
development over the last decade and more since it started the 
policy of reform and opening up. However, it still has a long 
way to go before it can truly become prosperous. "We are 
striving for sustained, rapid, and healthy economic development. 
Therefore, we need a peaceful international environment and a 
stable political and social order at home. While engaging in 
economic construction, we attach great importance to 
strengthening socialist democracy and the legal system." The 
CPPCC is playing an increasingly important role in this regard. 
  Li Ruihuan briefed Troedsson on the CPPCC's functions, 
status, and role. 
  Troedsson said: Swedish-Chinese relations have grown 
constantly in recent years with a constant expansion of 
bilateral cooperation, a constant increase in trade volume and 
investment projects, and very active cultural exchanges. The 
facts prove that cooperation and exchanges conform to the 
fundamental interests of the people of both countries. She 
said: Chairman Li Ruihuan is visiting Sweden at a time when the 
Swedish people are becoming more and more interested in China. 
This fact is no doubt very helpful to the mutual understanding 
between the two peoples and to the mutually beneficial 
cooperation between the two countries. 
  Troedsson gave a luncheon for Li Ruihuan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

