<H3> <TI>   NBC Correspondents Questioned Over Unauthorized Coverage </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NBC Correspondents Questioned Over Unauthorized Coverage </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1705130794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1256 GMT 17 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1705130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 17 (XINHUA) -- Two American 
correspondents were questioned for unauthorized news coverage 
this morning by Chinese department concerned according to law. 
  The two correspondents, Lucky Severson and Gary Fairman, are 
from the American National Broadcasting Corporation (NBC). They 
conducted news covering activities without first going through 
the prescribed formalities, said an official from the department. 
  The official said that the two correspondents admitted that 
they conducted news coverage without going through the required 
formalities and promised to obey Chinese laws and rules in 
future. 
  They were let go after the inquiry. 

</TEXT>

