<H3> <TI>   Rong Yiren Addresses Economic Conference's Opening </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rong Yiren Addresses Economic Conference's Opening </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1605085094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0830 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1605085094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 16 (XINHUA) -- The four-day China 
conference on market economy and trade opened here this morning. 
  Chinese Vice-President Rong Yiren attended the opening 
ceremony and delivered a congratulatory speech. 
  In his speech, Rong said that the United States has the most 
developed market economy in the Western world, and China is 
building its socialist market economy. 
  He continued that it is of great significance for experts, 
scholars and entrepreneurs of the two countries to get together 
to discuss and study issues concerning the market economy so as 
to enhance mutual understanding between the two countries. 
  President of the Chinese People's Association for Friendship 
With Foreign Countries Qi Huaiyuan, president of the China 
Market Economy Society Wang Jue, and president of the Foundation 
for International Cooperation and Development Norman Swanson 
also spoke at the opening ceremony. 
  Representatives from the Chinese Foreign Ministry, the 
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation and the China 
Council for the Promotion of International Trade Attended the 
opening ceremony. 
  About 300 representatives, including nearly 90 U.S. 
representatives from the fields of energy, communications, 
chemicals, aviation, textiles, computers and food processing, 
will hold discussions on issues of common interest such as 
securities and financial markets, banking and accounting 
principles, investment protection, joint ventures, real estate, 
traditional and non- traditional trade and taxation. 
  Business negotiations will also be held during the 
conference. 

</TEXT>

