<H3> <TI>   Fujian Governor Addresses Land Management Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fujian Governor Addresses Land Management Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1805003494 Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1805003494 </F>
<F P=104>  Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A provincial land management meeting opened in 
Fuzhou yesterday [12 May]. The main agenda of the meeting is: 
Summing up and exchanging our province's experiences in land 
management, and probing the way to further strengthen land 
management, speed up the establishment of land system, cultivate 
and develop a standardized real estate market, and so on. 
  Governor Chen Mingyi made an important speech at the 
meeting. 
Zou Yuchuan, director of the State Land Administrative Bureau, 
made a special trip to Fuzhou to attend and address the meeting. 
Other Fujian leaders who attended the meeting included You 
Dexin and Liu Yongye, and responsible persons from relevant 
departments directly under the provincial authorities, as well 
as leaders in charge of land management in various prefectures, 
cities, counties and districts. 
  At the meeting, Governor Chen Mingyi and other leaders 
presented awards to 79 advanced units that had been commended by 
the provincial government for doing well in 1993 in opening up 
cultivated land, and serving the project of developing 
cultivated land. 

</TEXT>

