<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Visits Northern European Countries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihuan Visits Northern European Countries </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets Swedish Prime Minister </H4>

<F P=102> OW1405181194 Beijing Central Television Program One Network 
in Mandarin 1100 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1405181194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing Central Television Program One Network 
in Mandarin 1100 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video; from the "National News </F>
Hookup" program] 
  [Text] On the morning of 10 May local time, Swedish Prime 
Minister Carl Bildt met with Li Ruihuan, chairman of the 
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference [CPPCC], in his office. 
  Li Ruihuan said: China and Sweden are far away from each 
other and have no conflict of basic interests. On the contrary, 
there are broad prospects for economic cooperation because the 
economies of the two countries are mutually complementary. 
China is carrying out large-scale economic development, and 
there is much in Sweden's advanced technology and management 
experience that we can make use of. During my visit to your 
country, I have personally witnessed Swedish entrepreneurs' 
desire to strengthen cooperation with China. Our two countries 
should exert joint efforts to push bilateral cooperation to a 
new stage, which corresponds with the common interests and 
aspirations of the two peoples. 
  The Swedish prime minister said that bilateral relations 
between China and Sweden have developed rapidly in recent years, 
and he expressed his hope that they will develop further. He 
also expressed Sweden's support for China's reentry into the 
GATT. [video shows Li and Bildt walking out of a room, then stop 
and stand side by side as photographers take pictures of them] 
  Around noon, Troedsson, speaker of the parliament of the 
Kingdom of Sweden, met with Chairman Li Ruihuan in the 
parliament building. Li Ruihuan said: While developing the 
economy, China pays great attention to promoting socialist 
democracy and legality. In this regard, the CPPCC is playing an 
increasingly important role. Speaker Troedsson said that 
experience has shown that Swedish- Chinese cooperation and 
exchanges are in accordance with the fundamental interest of the 
Swedish and Chinese peoples. [video shows Li and Troedsson 
standing together, with glasses in hand, and speaking through an 
interpreter] 
  In the afternoon, Chairman Li Ruihuan met with Swedish 
Minister of Foreign Trade Dinkelspiel. 
  After successfully concluding his visit to Sweden, Chairman 
Li Ruihuan left Stockholm by a special plane and, less than an 
hour later, arrived at (Kathmond) Airport in Oslo. Upon his 
arrival, Chairman Li Ruihuan said in a written statement that 
China attaches importance to developing exchanges and 
cooperation with Norway in all fields. China wishes to develop 
a long-term, stable friendship with Norway. 
  Bjorn Tore Godal, Norwegian acting prime minister and 
foreign 
minister, greeted Chairman Li Ruihuan and his entourage in the 
hall of the hotel where Chairman Li is staying. 
  Chairman Li Ruihuan is making an official goodwill visit to 
the Kingdom of Norway at the invitation of the Norwegian 
Government. 

</TEXT>

