<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Visits Northern European Countries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihuan Visits Northern European Countries </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Briefs Norwegian Businessmen </H4>

<F P=102> OW1305204894 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0345 
GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1305204894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Xu Furui (6079 4395 3848)] </F>
  [Text] Oslo, 11 May (XINHUA) -- At a meeting this afternoon 
with Norwegian entrepreneurs from industrial and commercial 
circles, Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the 
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, who is on an 
official friendly visit to Norway, briefed Norwegian 
entrepreneurs on China's achievements in reform and opening up 
and expressed the hope of developing reciprocal and cooperative 
relations between China and Norway. 
  He said: China is making efforts to establish a brand-new 
socialist market economic structure. In the progress of reform 
and opening up, China has significantly improved its investment 
environment, gradually amplified its economic laws and 
regulations, and expanded its investment scope. "From now on, 
we must continue to deepen reform, open wider to the outside 
world, and further improve the investment environment in order 
to offer favorable conditions to foreign entrepreneurs who come 
to China to promote economic cooperation." 
  Li Ruihuan said: In recent years, economic and trade 
exchanges and cooperation in other fields between China and 
Norway have developed rapidly. However, in light of the 
supplementary nature and strength of both economies, the 
potential for bilateral cooperation is still great. He added: 
I welcome more Norwegian entrepreneurs to invest in China and 
to establish more foreign- funded enterprises. I hope that 
entrepreneurs from Norwegian economic circles will formulate 
long-term strategies and foster an enterprising spirit to 
explore more fields of cooperation with China. 
  Schel Kultin [name as received], secretary general of the 
Norwegian Foreign Ministry, presided over the meeting. He said: 
Chairman Li Ruihuan's visit has helped Norwegian enterprises 
understand China's economic development, and his visit is 
conducive to promoting the development of reciprocal and 
cooperative relations between Norway and China. He expressed 
his hope that Chairman Li Ruihuan's visit will further promote 
the development of bilateral economic and trade relations based 
on the existing foundation. Entrepreneurs from Norway's 
industrial and commercial circles introduced the strong points 
of their enterprises and the development of cooperation with 
Chinese enterprises. They offered suggestions as well. 

</TEXT>

