  [Text] Copenhagen, 14 May (XINHUA) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman 
of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference, met staff of the Chinese Embassy in 
Denmark and representatives of the Chinese community and 
students here on 14 May, and had cordial conversations with them. 
  Li Ruihuan called on embassy staff to make more friends and 
work harder to help create a sustained, fine, and peaceful 
international environment for China's economic development. He 
also expressed the hope that the Chinese community in Denmark 
will make use of its favorable conditions to do something for 
China. In his conversations with representatives of Chinese 
students, Li Ruihuan said that although Denmark is a small 
country lacking resources, it possesses many advanced 
technologies and strong points for us to study and master. 
  After the meeting, Li Ruihuan also separately posed for 
photographs with the attendees. 

