<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meeting Releases Statistics on Foreign Investment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meeting Releases Statistics on Foreign Investment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1505043494 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0732 GMT 
14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1505043494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 14 (CNS) -- According to a working 
meeting for registration of foreign-funded enterprises recently 
held here, after 15 years of reform and opening to the outside 
world, by the end of 1993, more than 170,000 foreign-funded 
enterprises have registered in China, with a total investment of 
U.S.$382.4 billion and a total registered capital of U.S.$245.6 
billion, and of which U.S.$150.0 billion was foreign investment. 
Some 146 countries and regions have invested in China, and 
China's absorption of foreign capital has made up 40 percent of 
the total by developing countries. 
  By the end of last year, actual foreign investment in China 
was U.S.$56 billion. Foreign investment in place in China made 
up 13 percent of the total social fixed asset investment in the 
country, up from 2.5 percent in 1980s. The output value of 
foreign-funded industrial enterprises last year was RMB 302 
billion [renminbi], making up 9.6 percent of the Gross Domestic 
Product (GDP) in the country. 

</TEXT>

