BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, May 17 (CNS) -- Guangzhou, capital of 
Guangdong Province, earned export value of U.S.$1.097 billion in 
the first four months this year, 32 percent up over the same 
period of last year. 
  Enterprises engaging in foreign trade in the city have 
developed their businesses from single way of foreign trade to 
diversified businesses including domestic trade, real estate and 
manufacturing other than foreign trade. Its construction of 
production bases for export products have been further 
strengthened, its international business further developed and 
the market structure for its export improved with its exports to 
the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) countries in 
the first quarter this year increased by 70.63 percent over the 
same period of last year, that to African countries by 111.97 
percent, that to the Middle East countries by 89.56 percent, 
that to the South American countries by 77.45 percent and that 
to neighboring countries by 155.79 percent. 

