<H4>    Further on Li's Speech </H4>

<F P=102> OW1705134594 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0950 
GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1705134594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Feature by RENMIN RIBAO reporter Chen Weiwei (7115 4850 </F>
0251) and XINHUA reporter He Ping (0149 1627): "Hold High the 
Banner of the Shock Brigade -- Li Ruihuan Meeting With 
Representatives of Old and Young Shock Brigades"] 
  [Excerpts] Beijing, 28 Apr (XINHUA) -- Two generations of 
shock brigade leaders in the capital today happily gathered at 
the Beijing International Convention Center, with each wearing a 
big bright-colored red flower on his chest. At 0900, when Li 
Ruihuan, member of the Standing Committee of the CPC Central 
Committee Political Bureau, and Zhang Baifa, executive deputy 
mayor of Beijing, entered the center, all those present gave 
warm applause to them who both served as leaders of shock 
brigades well-known throughout the country in the 1950s. 
[passage omitted] 
  Youth shock brigades came into being in the 1950s as 
national 
economic construction was on the upsurge. In the new situation 
brought about by reform and opening-up, the banner of the shock 
brigade has become ever more resplendent, under which a large 
number of young pioneering workers have emerged. [passage 
omitted] 
  On behalf of the younger generation, Li Keqiang, first 
secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Youth 
League, asked the older generation to rest assured that the 
younger generation would carry forward the fine tradition of the 
older generation and that the banner of the shock brigade would 
fly high into the next century. 
  Forty years elapsed in the twinkling of an eye. Recalling 
the past and comparing it with the present, Li Ruihuan was 
excited. He said: "Tremendous changes have taken place in our 
country over the past 40 years. During these years, youth shock 
brigades in the capital have made outstanding contributions to 
the construction of the city, winning honor for building 
workers, for Beijing residents, and for the Chinese people. 
Youth shock brigades have scored marked achievements, gained a 
wealth of experience, trained a large number of qualified 
personnel, and formed fine traditions and work style. I hope 
that you carry forward all such good things and develop them." 
  Liu Ruihuan then said: "The new situation has set new 
requirements for us. I hope that while carrying forward the 
tradition, you will gain fresh, more useful experiences. You 
should not only do a good job in building houses and roads but 
also step up your ideological education. A new generation of 
well-educated, well-disciplined people with lofty ideals and 
moral values should be cultivated. It is hoped that the younger 
generation is better and stronger than the older one." 
  Words with deep feeling and ardent exhortation! 
  When Li Ruihuan finished his speech, the audience responded 
with warm applause. 

</TEXT>

