<H3> <TI>   Li Lanqing Arrives in Singapore To Address Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Lanqing Arrives in Singapore To Address Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1805163194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1501 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1805163194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Singapore, May 18 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice Premier 
Li Lanqing arrived here today to attend the ongoing 
international conference on Southeast Asia, Vietnam and China, 
and the inaugural meeting of the joint steering council on the 
Suzhou industrial township project. 
  Li will deliver a keynote address at the international 
conference, known as "Waves of the Future - ASEAN, Vietnam and 
China: Opportunities for World Business" on Thursday [19 May]. 
  The conference, started on Tuesday, is being attended by 
some 
800 delegates from 21 countries and regions around the world. 
Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong, New Zealand Prime 
Minister James Bolger, Vietnamese Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet, 
Singapore Senior Minister Lee Kuan Yew are among the speakers at 
the conference. 
  During his four-day stay, Li will also chair jointly with 
his 
Singapore counterpart Lee Hsien Loong the inaugural joint 
steering council meeting on the Suzhou industrial township 
project on Friday. 

