<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Visits University, Companies in Demark </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihuan Visits University, Companies in Demark </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1905105894 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1504 
GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1905105894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Wu Ping (0702 1627)] </F>
  [Text] Copenhagen, 17 May (XINHUA) -- Li Ruihuan, 
chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's 
Political Consultative Conference, was accorded a warm and 
friendly reception when he visited the Royal Danish University 
for Veterinary Science and Agriculture and the Nuovo Corporation 
this morning. 
  The Royal Danish University for Veterinary Science and 
Agriculture is Denmark's only institute of higher learning for 
agriculture as well as one of Europe's oldest agricultural 
colleges. 
  In the company of University President Dr. (Ben ser 
Nielsen), 
Li Ruihuan visited the university's veterinary studies 
department and heard a general briefing on the university. Dr. 
Nielsen expressed his hope for strengthened educational and 
scientific and technological exchanges between Danish and 
Chinese universities. 
  Later, Li Ruihuan visited the world-famous Nuovo 
Corporation. 
Last year the corporation recorded a business turnover of 12.2 
billion kroner and captured a world market share of 50 percent 
for its insulin and over 40 percent for its enzyme products, 
respectively. 
  In the afternoon Li Ruihuan visited Denmark's largest 
foodstuff producer -- the (Danisco) Corporation. 

</TEXT>

