<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, May 17 (XINHUA) -- Hungary is willing to 
expand cooperation with China in economy and military projects, 
Hungarian President Arpad Goncz told Zhang Wannian, chief of the 
General Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army, here 
today. 
  During a meeting with General Zhang, Goncz said Hungary is 
ready to deepen its cooperation with China, which has witnessed 
phenomenal economic growth in recent years. 
  The president said Zhang's visit will contribute to the 
further development of cooperative ties between the two 
countries and between their armed forces. 
  The Chinese general, who arrived here last Friday [13 May] 
for a five-day visit to Hungary, said he is confident that the 
relations of cooperation between the armed forces of the two 
countries will grow to a new level. 
  Prior to Hungary, Zhang visited Romania and Poland. 

