<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Editorial Promotes `Civil Affairs' Work </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Editorial Promotes `Civil Affairs' Work </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1805120094 Beijing RENMIN RIBAO in Chinese 17 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> HK1805120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing RENMIN RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Editorial: "Pursue Civil Affairs Satisfactorily, Promote </F>
Social Stability and Development"] 
  [Text] The 10th National Civil Affairs Conference, which 
was convened by the State Council, ended today. Party and 
government leaders and civil affairs workers gathered together 
to discuss plans for reforming and developing civil affairs 
work. These discussions will play an active role in reforming, 
developing, and promoting social stability. We warmly 
congratulate the convocation of the conference. 
  Civil affairs is a key work area for the party and 
government. Following the Third Plenary Session of the 11th 
Central Committee, civil affairs departments at all levels, 
guided by Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism 
with Chinese characteristics and the party's basic line and led 
by the party and government, have revolved closely around 
economic construction and have self- consciously linked civil 
affairs work closely with the country's economic development and 
social stability, taken the job of ensuring the well-being of 
the daily lives of people -- the target of civil affairs work -- 
as a mission basic to the maintenance of social stability, 
upheld reforms, worked in a down-to-earth manner, and played a 
key role in creating a stable, unified, democratic, and 
harmonious social environment beneficial to socialist 
modernization. Reform has injected vitality into civil affairs 
work. Reform in disaster relief management and the unfolding of 
social old-age insurance in rural areas has promoted the 
development of social security in rural areas. Flourishing 
community services have brought a new outlook for urban social 
welfare services, and the activity of competing for the creation 
of "two-support" model towns (counties) has opened a new 
dimension in welfare work to provide preferential treatment, 
pensions, and home placements. Civil affairs work has scored 
various long-term achievements and is vibrant and flourishing. 
  The Central Committee has stressed that seizing 
opportunities, deepening reforms, expanding opening up, 
promoting development, and maintaining stability is the overall 
framework for party and government work. Civil affairs work is 
a key integral part of government work. We must resolutely obey 
and serve this overall framework, fully exercise the functions 
of civil affairs departments, and satisfactorily pursue rescue 
and relief work, social welfare, the work of providing 
preferential treatment, pensions, and home placement, the 
construction of grass-roots political power and mass self-rule 
organizations, rural social old-age insurance, and social 
welfare and social management work, such as that concerning 
community bodies, marriages, child adoption, and funerals. The 
main responsibility of civil affairs work is to safeguard and 
protect, with state-given powers and according to the law, the 
people's basic living rights and interests. It represents a 
basic demand of socialism and shows the superiority of the 
socialist system. 
  Civil affairs work concerns thousands of households and is 
connected with people's lives, intimately related to various 
socialist modernization projects, and strongly social in 
character. It involves mass participation. Civil affairs work 
departments must understand and study new situations emerging 
under the socialist market economy system, sum up new 
experiences, and solve new problems. Party committees and 
governments at all levels must strengthen leadership and put it 
high on their agenda. Concerned departments must care about and 
support civil affairs work and mobilize forces in various social 
sectors in a joint effort at civil affairs work. Its missions 
are arduous and responsibility great. We are convinced that 
guided by Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism 
with Chinese characteristics and the spirit of the 14th CPC 
Congress, and led by the party Central Committee and the State 
Council, civil affairs work will score greater achievements and 
make new contributions toward maintaining social stability and 
promoting socialist material and spiritual civilizations. 

</TEXT>

