<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   China Land, Real Estate Market Established </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    China Land, Real Estate Market Established </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1905065694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0627 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1905065694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 19 (XINHUA) -- The China Land and Real 
Estate Market was set up here Wednesday [18 May] with the 
approval of the State Bureau of Land Administration and the 
State Commission for Restructuring the Economy. 
  Members of the market will include administrative 
institutions, commercial organizations and large commercial and 
development companies dealing in land and real estate at all 
levels. 
  The market will engage in governmental selling of land-use 
rights, businessmen's transfer of land use rights and real 
estate transactions. Its business scope includes agency work, 
appraisal, advertising, market surveys, estate planning, 
information, legal consultation and international exchanges. 
  At the same time, China's first fair featuring land and real 
estate opened here. Attending the fair were representatives 
from over 60 large real estate companies throughout the country 
and delegations from northwest China's Shaanxi Province, south 
China's Haikou city and southwest China's Chongqing city. 

</TEXT>

