<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Preparatory Work Starts on Central China Railway Line </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Preparatory Work Starts on Central China Railway Line </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1905065994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0638 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1905065994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shijiazhuang, May 19 (XINHUA) -- Preparatory work 
has started on the construction of a new trunk railway line from 
Handan city, in north China's Hebei Province, to Jinan, 
provincial capital of east China's Shandong Province. 
  The new railway line will have a total length of 234 km and 
will be jointly constructed by Hebei and Shandong provinces and 
the Ministry of Railways, with a total investment of 1.53 
billion yuan (about 175.86 million U.S. dollars). 
  The construction will be carried out in two phases -- a 
single line for the first-phase construction and double-tracking 
in the second phase. 
  When it is completed, the new railway line, the west end of 
which be linked to the existing coal transport railway lines to 
Shanxi Province, China's leading coal producer, will help 
transport 20 million tons of goods a year, and three pairs of 
passenger trains will be able to operate on the line a day. 
  Experts here say the construction of the new railway is of 
special importance not only for transporting coal from Shanxi 
but also for further improving transportation conditions in the 
hinterland of China. 

</TEXT>

