<F P=100> Northwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qinghai Province Increases Exports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qinghai Province Increases Exports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1905030294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0230 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1905030294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Xining, May 19 (XINHUA) -- Northwest China's 
Qinghai Province had exported 35.81 million U.S. dollars-worth 
of commodities by May 10, an increase of 39.5 percent compared 
with the corresponding period of last year. 
  The increase rate is also higher than the national growth 
rate of 22 percent for exports in the past four months, said 
local trade officials. 
  Meanwhile, imports in the same period were worth 11.92 
million U.S. dollars, a decrease of 40,000 U.S. dollars over the 
same period of last year. 
  The officials attributed the growth in exports in the first 
four months of this year to the implementation of reform 
measures in foreign trade. 
  They said they believed that the unification of foreign 
exchange rates and other foreign trade reform measures have 
provided favorable conditions for the development of enterprises 
engaged in foreign trade and have brought the enthusiasm of 
these enterprises into full play. 

</TEXT>

