<H3> <TI>   Urumqi Sentences Railway Worker To Death for Theft </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Urumqi Sentences Railway Worker To Death for Theft </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1805142094 Beijing Central People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1030 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1805142094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing Central People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National Hookup" program] </F>
  [Text] The Urumqi Railway Intermediate People's Court 
recently announced judgment on a serious case of theft committed 
by a unit's own staff members. The chief culprit (Ou Qilin) was 
sentenced to death in accordance with the law. 
  From the end of 1992 to the end of 1993, (Ou Qilin), a 
former 
commodity inspector of Sulehe station, Liuyuan Locomotive 
Section, took advantage of his position to repeatedly steal more 
than 60 kinds of railway transportation materials in 
collaboration with other people, with a total value of 70,000 
yuan. He himself took goods worth more than 30,000 yuan and was 
sentenced to death. 
  From March to August last year, (Bao Yunhai), a cleaner of 
Qiaowan station, Liuyuan Locomotive Section, repeatedly stole 14 
kinds of transportation materials in collaboration with other 
people, with a total value 43,000 yuan. He himself took goods 
worth some 20,000 yuan and was sentenced to life imprisonment. 
  (Hu Wenjun), (Liu Xinting), (Hao Shaowen), (Chen Yuanwen), 
and (Gao Shangyou) who also took part in the activities, were 
sentenced to imprisonment. 

</TEXT>

