<F P=103> OW1805040194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Urumqi, May 18 (XINHUA) -- The airline of northwest 
China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region will operate three new 
international or regional air routes beginning in June this year. 
  According to local officials, the routes are 
Tianjin-Urumqi-Novosibirsk-Moscow, Urumqi-Islamabad and 
Urumqi-Chongqing-Hong Kong. 
  The Tianjin-Urumqi-Novosibirsk-Moscow and Urumqi-Islamabad 
routes will have their maiden flights on June 10 and July 10, 
respectively. There will be one flight a week by TU-154s on each 
of the air routes. 
  Charter flights will be available on the route from Urumqi 
to 
Hong Kong via Chongqing, and there will be only one flight a 
week, said the officials. 

