<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Inspection Group To Visit Subic Bay 24-26 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Inspection Group To Visit Subic Bay 24-26 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1905094294 Taipei CNA in English 0800 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1905094294 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Danielle Yang] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, May 19 (CNA) -- The Chinese National 
Federation of Industries will send a 60-member delegation to the 
Philippines' Subic Bay May 24-26 to inspect potential investment 
sites, a federation official said Thursday [19 May]. 
  Vice Secretary-General Chen Chin-nan said the group members 
will seek to understand labor problems there and consult with 
Philippine authorities on the business tax they will collect 
from Taiwan investors. 
  Chen said as the Philippines has frequent labor disputes and 
strikes, Taiwan investors are concerned about whether there will 
be similar incidents when they set up business there. 
  Investment in Subic Bay is one part of the government's 
"southern strategy," which encourages Taiwan investment in 
Southeast Asia. 

</TEXT>

